### 7. Repository Pattern

All repositories extend `MongoRepository<Entity, String>`:

**Example: WWorldRepository**
File: `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/server/world-shared/src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/shared/world/WWorldRepository.java`

```java
@Repository
public interface WWorldRepository extends MongoRepository<WWorld, String> {
    Optional<WWorld> findByWorldId(String worldId);
    boolean existsByWorldId(String worldId);
    List<WWorld> findByRegionId(String regionId);

    @Query("{ $or: [ " +
            "{ 'worldId': { $regex: ?0, $options: 'i' } }, " +
            "{ 'name': { $regex: ?0, $options: 'i' } }, " +
            "{ 'description': { $regex: ?0, $options: 'i' } } " +
            "] }")
    Page<WWorld> findBySearchQuery(String searchPattern, Pageable pageable);
}
```

**Example: WEntityRepository**
```java
@Repository
public interface WEntityRepository extends MongoRepository<WEntity, String> {
    Optional<WEntity> findByWorldIdAndEntityId(String worldId, String entityId);
    List<WEntity> findByWorldId(String worldId);
    List<WEntity> findByWorldIdAndModelId(String worldId, String modelId);
    List<WEntity> findByWorldIdAndEnabled(String worldId, boolean enabled);
}
```

### 8. Service Pattern

All services use `@Service` annotation with dependency injection and transactional methods:

**Example: WWorldService**
File: `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/server/world-shared/src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/shared/world/WWorldService.java`

```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Slf4j
public class WWorldService {
    private final WWorldRepository repository;

    @Transactional(readOnly = true)
    public Optional<WWorld> getByWorldId(WorldId worldId) {
        return repository.findByWorldId(worldId.getId());
    }

    @Transactional
    public WWorld createWorld(WorldId worldId, WorldInfo info) {
        if (repository.existsByWorldId(worldId.getId())) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("WorldId already exists");
        }
        WWorld entity = WWorld.builder()
                .worldId(worldId.getId())
                .publicData(info)
                .build();
        entity.touchForCreate();
        return repository.save(entity);
    }

    @Transactional
    public Optional<WWorld> updateWorld(WorldId worldId, Consumer<WWorld> updater) {
        return repository.findByWorldId(worldId.getId()).map(existing -> {
            updater.accept(existing);
            existing.touchForUpdate();
            return repository.save(existing);
        });
    }
}
```

**Example: WEntityService**
File: `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/server/world-shared/src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/shared/world/WEntityService.java`

```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Slf4j
public class WEntityService {
    private final WEntityRepository repository;

    @Transactional
    public WEntity save(WorldId worldId, String entityId, Entity publicData, String modelId) {
        WEntity entity = repository.findByWorldIdAndEntityId(worldId.getId(), entityId)
            .orElseGet(() -> {
                WEntity neu = WEntity.builder()
                        .worldId(worldId.getId())
                        .entityId(entityId)
                        .modelId(modelId)
                        .enabled(true)
                        .build();
                neu.touchCreate();
                return neu;
            });

        entity.setPublicData(publicData);
        entity.setModelId(modelId);
        entity.touchUpdate();
        return repository.save(entity);
    }

    @Transactional
    public Optional<WEntity> update(WorldId worldId, String entityId, Consumer<WEntity> updater) {
        return repository.findByWorldIdAndEntityId(worldId.getId(), entityId)
            .map(entity -> {
                updater.accept(entity);
                entity.touchUpdate();
                return repository.save(entity);
            });
    }
}
```

### 9. MongoDB Index Definitions

Entities use compound indexes for efficient queries:

**WWorld:**
```java
@Document(collection = "worlds")
```

**WEntity:**
```java
@CompoundIndexes({
    @CompoundIndex(name = "worldId_entityId_idx", 
                   def = "{ 'worldId': 1, 'entityId': 1 }", 
                   unique = true)
})
```

**WItemPosition:**
```java
@CompoundIndexes({
    @CompoundIndex(name = "world_itemId_idx", 
                   def = "{ 'worldId': 1, 'itemId': 1 }", 
                   unique = true)
})
```

**WLayer:**
```java
@CompoundIndexes({
    @CompoundIndex(name = "world_name_idx", 
                   def = "{ 'worldId': 1, 'name': 1 }", 
                   unique = true),
    @CompoundIndex(name = "world_order_idx", 
                   def = "{ 'worldId': 1, 'order': 1 }"),
    @CompoundIndex(name = "world_enabled_idx", 
                   def = "{ 'worldId': 1, 'enabled': 1 }")
})
```

### 10. Key Technical Characteristics

**Architecture Patterns:**
- Clean separation: Entities wrap generated DTOs in `publicData` field
- All inbound validation happens in controllers
- Services handle business logic and transactions
- Repositories handle data persistence only
- No JSON manipulation - all data typed

**MongoDB Integration:**
- Spring Data MongoDB with MongoRepository
- Compound indexes for query optimization
- Soft deletes via `enabled` flag
- String IDs with MongoDB ObjectId mapping
- Schema versioning via `@ActualSchemaVersion`

**Generated Module Contract:**
- WorldInfo, Entity, EntityModel, Item, BlockType all from generated module
- HexVector2 and HexGrid for hex coordinate support
- Automatic serialization/deserialization via Jackson annotations
- Contract between Java backend and TypeScript frontend

**Service Layer Pattern:**
- `@Transactional` for transaction management
- `@RequiredArgsConstructor` for dependency injection
- Read-only transactions for queries
- Consumer pattern for updates (functional programming)
- Comprehensive logging with `@Slf4j`

**Dependencies (pom.xml):**
- Spring Boot 3 with Data MongoDB and Redis
- Spring Data for repository pattern
- Lombok for boilerplate reduction
- Generated module for contract types
- Shared module for common utilities

### 11. Entry Point Structure

**WEntryPoint:**
File: `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/server/world-shared/src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/shared/world/WEntryPoint.java`

```java
@Data
@Builder
public class WEntryPoint {
    private String name;
    private Area area;  // Reference to Area from generated module
}
```

Entry points are stored in WWorld as a List:
```java
@Builder.Default
private List<WEntryPoint> entryPoints = List.of();
```

This comprehensive exploration shows a well-structured, clean architecture with consistent patterns throughout the world-shared module, proper use of MongoDB annotations, clear entity-repository-service separation, and proper integration with generated types from the generated module.

