#### 2.4 Algorithmus: getFlatPositionSet()

**Ansatz:** Bounding Box + Point-in-Hexagon Test

```java
public Set<FlatPosition> getFlatPositionSet(WWorld worldEntity) {
    int gridSize = worldEntity.getPublicData().getHexGridSize();
    HexVector2 hexPos = this.publicData.getPosition();

    // 1. Calculate hex center in cartesian coordinates
    double centerX = ...;
    double centerZ = ...;

    // 2. Calculate bounding box (rectangular area containing hex)
    int minX = (int) Math.floor(centerX - gridSize);
    int maxX = (int) Math.ceil(centerX + gridSize);
    int minZ = (int) Math.floor(centerZ - gridSize);
    int maxZ = (int) Math.ceil(centerZ + gridSize);

    // 3. Test each point in bounding box
    Set<FlatPosition> positions = new HashSet<>();
    for (int x = minX; x <= maxX; x++) {
        for (int z = minZ; z <= maxZ; z++) {
            if (isPointInHex(x, z, centerX, centerZ, gridSize)) {
                positions.add(new FlatPosition(x, z));
            }
        }
    }

    return positions;
}

private boolean isPointInHex(int x, int z, double hexCenterX, double hexCenterZ, int gridSize) {
    // Convert point to hex-relative coordinates
    double dx = x - hexCenterX;
    double dz = z - hexCenterZ;

    // Pointy-top hexagon test
    // Use cube coordinate constraints
    double q = (sqrt(3)/3 * dx - 1/3 * dz);
    double r = (2/3 * dz);
    double s = -q - r;

    // Point is inside if all cube coords are within radius
    double radius = gridSize / 2.0;
    return Math.abs(q) <= radius && 
           Math.abs(r) <= radius && 
           Math.abs(s) <= radius;
}
```

