### 5. DETAILLIERTE HEX-MATHEMATIK

#### 5.1 Pointy-Top Hexagon Layout

```
    top
   /   \
 NW     NE
|         |
|  (q,r)  |
|         |
 SW     SE
   \   /
   bottom
```

**Hex-Vertices (pointy-top, radius=1):**
- 0°: (0, -1) top
- 60°: (√3/2, -1/2) 
- 120°: (√3/2, 1/2)
- 180°: (0, 1) bottom
- 240°: (-√3/2, 1/2)
- 300°: (-√3/2, -1/2)

#### 5.2 Hex Center zu Cartesian (für gridSize Durchmesser)

```java
public static double[] hexToCartesian(HexVector2 hex, int gridSize) {
    double radius = gridSize / 2.0;
    double x = radius * Math.sqrt(3) * (hex.getQ() + hex.getR() / 2.0);
    double z = radius * (3.0 / 2.0) * hex.getR();
    return new double[]{x, z};
}
```

#### 5.3 Point-in-Hexagon Test (Cube Coordinates)

```java
public static boolean isPointInHex(double x, double z, double hexCenterX, double hexCenterZ, int gridSize) {
    double radius = gridSize / 2.0;

    // Transform to hex-relative coordinates
    double dx = x - hexCenterX;
    double dz = z - hexCenterZ;

    // Convert to cube coordinates (fractional)
    double q = (Math.sqrt(3)/3.0 * dx - 1.0/3.0 * dz) / radius;
    double r = (2.0/3.0 * dz) / radius;
    double s = -q - r;

    // Point is inside if all cube coordinate magnitudes <= 1
    return Math.abs(q) <= 1.0 && Math.abs(r) <= 1.0 && Math.abs(s) <= 1.0;
}
```

### 6. ERROR HANDLING & VALIDATION

**Entity Level:**
- `publicData` darf nicht null sein beim Save
