**Algorithmus** (basierend auf NormalGenerator.ts):
```java
@Component
public class NormalWorldGenerator extends AbstractTerrainGenerator {

    private static final Logger log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(NormalWorldGenerator.class);

    // Parameter keys
    public static final String PARAM_WATER_LEVEL = "waterLevel";
    public static final String PARAM_BASE_HEIGHT = "baseHeight";
    public static final String PARAM_HEIGHT_VARIATION = "heightVariation";
    public static final String PARAM_SEED = "seed";
    public static final String PARAM_GRASS_BLOCK_TYPE_ID = "grassBlockTypeId";
    public static final String PARAM_DIRT_BLOCK_TYPE_ID = "dirtBlockTypeId";
    public static final String PARAM_SAND_BLOCK_TYPE_ID = "sandBlockTypeId";
    public static final String PARAM_WATER_BLOCK_TYPE_ID = "waterBlockTypeId";

    // Noise scales (from NormalGenerator.ts)
    private static final double SCALE_1 = 0.01;  // Large hills
    private static final double SCALE_2 = 0.05;  // Medium features
    private static final double SCALE_3 = 0.1;   // Detail

    // Configuration
    private int waterLevel = 62;
    private int baseHeight = 64;
    private int heightVariation = 32;
    private long seed;

    private String grassBlockTypeId = "w/310";
    private String dirtBlockTypeId = "w/279";
    private String sandBlockTypeId = "w/520";
    private String waterBlockTypeId = "w/5000";

    // Noise generator
    private FastNoiseLite noise;

    @Override
    public String getExecutorName() {
        return "normal-world-generator";
    }

    @Override
    protected void configureGenerator(Map<String, String> genParams) {
        waterLevel = getIntParameter(genParams, PARAM_WATER_LEVEL, 62);
        baseHeight = getIntParameter(genParams, PARAM_BASE_HEIGHT, 64);
        heightVariation = getIntParameter(genParams, PARAM_HEIGHT_VARIATION, 32);
        seed = Long.parseLong(genParams.getOrDefault(PARAM_SEED, String.valueOf(System.currentTimeMillis())));

        grassBlockTypeId = genParams.getOrDefault(PARAM_GRASS_BLOCK_TYPE_ID, "w/310");
        dirtBlockTypeId = genParams.getOrDefault(PARAM_DIRT_BLOCK_TYPE_ID, "w/279");
        sandBlockTypeId = genParams.getOrDefault(PARAM_SAND_BLOCK_TYPE_ID, "w/520");
        waterBlockTypeId = genParams.getOrDefault(PARAM_WATER_BLOCK_TYPE_ID, "w/5000");

        // Initialize noise generator
        noise = new FastNoiseLite((int) seed);
        noise.SetNoiseType(FastNoiseLite.NoiseType.OpenSimplex2);
        noise.SetFrequency(1.0f);

        log.info("NormalWorldGenerator configured: waterLevel={}, baseHeight={}, heightVariation={}, seed={}", 
                 waterLevel, baseHeight, heightVariation, seed);
    }

    @Override
    protected int getTerrainHeight(int worldX, int worldZ) {
        // Multiple octaves (from NormalGenerator.ts lines 96-112)
        double noise1 = noise.GetNoise(worldX * SCALE_1, worldZ * SCALE_1);
        double noise2 = noise.GetNoise(worldX * SCALE_2, worldZ * SCALE_2);
        double noise3 = noise.GetNoise(worldX * SCALE_3, worldZ * SCALE_3);

        // Combine octaves with weights
        double combined = noise1 * 0.6 + noise2 * 0.3 + noise3 * 0.1;

        // Convert to height
        double height = baseHeight + combined * heightVariation;

        return (int) Math.floor(height);
    }

    @Override
    protected int generateTerrain(WWorld world, WHexGrid hexGrid, GeneratorContext context) {
        // Calculate bounding box for hex grid
        Iterable<FlatPosition> positions = hexGrid.getFlatPositionSet(world);

        // Pre-calculate height map with border (needed for smoothing)
        // Find bounds first
        int minX = Integer.MAX_VALUE, maxX = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        int minZ = Integer.MAX_VALUE, maxZ = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for (FlatPosition pos : positions) {
            minX = Math.min(minX, pos.x());
            maxX = Math.max(maxX, pos.x());
            minZ = Math.min(minZ, pos.z());
            maxZ = Math.max(maxZ, pos.z());
        }

        // Build height map with 1-block border for offset calculation
        int[][] heightMap = new int[maxX - minX + 3][maxZ - minZ + 3];
        for (int x = minX - 1; x <= maxX + 1; x++) {
            for (int z = minZ - 1; z <= maxZ + 1; z++) {
                heightMap[x - minX + 1][z - minZ + 1] = getTerrainHeight(x, z);
            }
        }

        // Group blocks by chunk
        Map<String, List<LayerBlock>> chunkBlocks = new HashMap<>();

        // Generate blocks for each position
        for (FlatPosition pos : positions) {
            int localX = pos.x() - minX + 1;
            int localZ = pos.z() - minZ + 1;
            int terrainHeight = heightMap[localX][localZ];

            String chunkKey = world.getChunkKey(pos.x(), pos.z());

            // Surface block (grass or sand)
            String surfaceBlockId = terrainHeight <= waterLevel ? sandBlockTypeId : grassBlockTypeId;
            Block surfaceBlock = createBlock(pos.x(), terrainHeight, pos.z(), surfaceBlockId);
            applyOffsets(surfaceBlock, localX, terrainHeight, localZ, heightMap, terrainHeight);
            chunkBlocks.computeIfAbsent(chunkKey, k -> new ArrayList<>())
                      .add(createLayerBlock(surfaceBlock));

            // Subsurface block (dirt)
            if (terrainHeight > 0) {
                Block dirtBlock = createBlock(pos.x(), terrainHeight - 1, pos.z(), dirtBlockTypeId);
                applyOffsets(dirtBlock, localX, terrainHeight - 1, localZ, heightMap, terrainHeight);
                chunkBlocks.computeIfAbsent(chunkKey, k -> new ArrayList<>())
                          .add(createLayerBlock(dirtBlock));
            }

            // Water block if below water level
            if (terrainHeight < waterLevel) {
                Block waterBlock = createBlock(pos.x(), waterLevel, pos.z(), waterBlockTypeId);
                chunkBlocks.computeIfAbsent(chunkKey, k -> new ArrayList<>())
                          .add(createLayerBlock(waterBlock));
            }
        }

        // Save all chunks
        int totalBlocks = 0;
        for (Map.Entry<String, List<LayerBlock>> entry : chunkBlocks.entrySet()) {
            saveChunk(context.worldId(), context.layerDataId(), entry.getKey(), entry.getValue());
            totalBlocks += entry.getValue().size();
        }

        return totalBlocks;
    }

    private void applyOffsets(Block block, int localX, int y, int localZ, int[][] heightMap, int centerHeight) {
        List<Float> offsets = calculateOffsets(localX, y, localZ, heightMap, centerHeight);
        if (offsets != null && !offsets.isEmpty()) {
            block.setOffsets(offsets);
        }
    }

    @Override
    protected List<Float> calculateOffsets(int x, int y, int z, int[][] heightMap, int centerHeight) {
        // Based on NormalGenerator.ts lines 263-342

        // Get heights of 8 neighbors + center
        int h_nw = getHeight(heightMap, x - 1, z - 1, centerHeight);
        int h_n = getHeight(heightMap, x, z - 1, centerHeight);
        int h_ne = getHeight(heightMap, x + 1, z - 1, centerHeight);
        int h_w = getHeight(heightMap, x - 1, z, centerHeight);
        int h_e = getHeight(heightMap, x + 1, z, centerHeight);
        int h_sw = getHeight(heightMap, x - 1, z + 1, centerHeight);
        int h_s = getHeight(heightMap, x, z + 1, centerHeight);
        int h_se = getHeight(heightMap, x + 1, z + 1, centerHeight);

        // Calculate offsets for 8 corners (24 values: 8 corners × 3 axes)
        List<Float> offsets = new ArrayList<>(24);
        for (int i = 0; i < 24; i++) offsets.add(0.0f);

        // Bottom corners - Y offset only
        float yDiff = y - centerHeight;
        float bottomOffset = Math.max(-1.0f, Math.min(1.0f, yDiff * 0.3f));

        // 4 bottom corners (indices 1, 4, 7, 10 are Y offsets)
        offsets.set(1, bottomOffset);   // left-back-bottom
        offsets.set(4, bottomOffset);   // right-back-bottom
        offsets.set(7, bottomOffset);   // right-front-bottom
        offsets.set(10, bottomOffset);  // left-front-bottom

        // Top corners - influenced by neighbors
        float topYDiff = y + 1 - centerHeight;
        float topOffset = Math.max(-1.0f, Math.min(1.0f, topYDiff * 0.3f));

        // left-back-top (influenced by W, NW, N)
        float h4 = (h_w + h_nw + h_n) / 3.0f;
        offsets.set(13, clamp((h4 - centerHeight) * 0.24f + topOffset));

        // right-back-top (influenced by E, NE, N)
        float h5 = (h_e + h_ne + h_n) / 3.0f;
        offsets.set(16, clamp((h5 - centerHeight) * 0.24f + topOffset));

        // right-front-top (influenced by E, SE, S)
        float h6 = (h_e + h_se + h_s) / 3.0f;
        offsets.set(19, clamp((h6 - centerHeight) * 0.24f + topOffset));

        // left-front-top (influenced by W, SW, S)
        float h7 = (h_w + h_sw + h_s) / 3.0f;
        offsets.set(22, clamp((h7 - centerHeight) * 0.24f + topOffset));

        // Check if any offset is non-zero
        boolean hasOffset = offsets.stream().anyMatch(o -> Math.abs(o) > 0.001f);
        return hasOffset ? offsets : null;
    }

    private int getHeight(int[][] heightMap, int x, int z, int defaultHeight) {
        try {
            return heightMap[x][z];
        } catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
            return defaultHeight;
        }
    }

    private float clamp(float value) {
        return Math.max(-1.0f, Math.min(1.0f, value));
    }

    private Block createBlock(int x, int y, int z, String blockTypeId) {
        return Block.builder()
            .blockTypeId(blockTypeId)
            .position(Vector3.builder().x(x).y(y).z(z).build())
            .rotation(RotationXY.builder().x(0).y(0).build())
            .build();
    }

    private LayerBlock createLayerBlock(Block block) {
        return LayerBlock.builder()
            .block(block)
            .weight(1)
            .override(true)
            .group(0)
            .build();
    }
}
```

#### 4. **HillyWorldGenerator**

**Datei**: `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/server/world-control/src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/control/generator/HillyWorldGenerator.java`

**Parameter-Konstanten**:
```java
public static final String PARAM_HILL_HEIGHT = "hillHeight";
public static final String PARAM_HILL_FREQUENCY = "hillFrequency";
public static final String PARAM_VALLEY_DEPTH = "valleyDepth";
public static final String PARAM_BASE_HEIGHT = "baseHeight";
```

**Unterschiede zu Normal**:
- Größere `heightVariation` (z.B. 64 statt 32)
- Andere Noise-Skalen für stärkere Hügel (z.B. SCALE_1 = 0.008)
- Stärkere Gewichtung der ersten Octave (0.7 statt 0.6)
- Steepness-Faktor für Offset-Berechnung

**Algorithmus**:
```java
@Component
public class HillyWorldGenerator extends AbstractTerrainGenerator {

    // Similar to NormalWorldGenerator but with:
    // - Different noise scales for more pronounced hills
    private static final double SCALE_1 = 0.008;  // Larger hills (smaller scale = larger features)
    private static final double SCALE_2 = 0.04;   // Medium features
    private static final double SCALE_3 = 0.08;   // Detail

    // - Higher weight on first octave
    private static final double WEIGHT_1 = 0.7;
    private static final double WEIGHT_2 = 0.2;
    private static final double WEIGHT_3 = 0.1;

    // - Larger default height variation
    private int heightVariation = 64;  // vs 32 in Normal

    // - Different offset calculation (steeper slopes)
    @Override
    protected List<Float> calculateOffsets(...) {
        // Use factor 0.35 instead of 0.24 for steeper terrain
        float h4 = (h_w + h_nw + h_n) / 3.0f;
        offsets.set(13, clamp((h4 - centerHeight) * 0.35f + topOffset));
        // ... etc
    }
}
```

### 5. **Dependency Management**

**pom.xml Ergänzung** für `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/server/world-control/pom.xml`:

```xml
<!-- Noise Library for Terrain Generation -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.github.tommyettinger</groupId>
    <artifactId>joise</artifactId>
    <version>1.1.0</version>
</dependency>
```

**Alternative**: FastNoiseLite als einzelne Java-Datei einbinden (keine Maven-Dependency nötig):
- Download von: https://github.com/Auburn/FastNoiseLite
- Datei: `FastNoiseLite.java` nach `src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/control/util/`

### 6. **Error Handling & Testing**

**Fehlerszenarien**:
1. **Missing Layer**: Wenn layer nicht existiert → JobResult.ofFailure("Layer not found: " + layerName)
2. **Invalid BlockTypeId**: Warnung loggen, Block überspringen
3. **Invalid Grid Position**: JobExecutionException werfen
4. **Memory Issues**: Chunk-basierte Verarbeitung verhindert OutOfMemory bei großen HexGrids

**Test-Strategie**:
- **Unit Tests**: Mock WWorldService, WHexGridService, WLayerService
- **Integration Tests**: Mit echter MongoDB und Layer-Speicherung
- **Performance Tests**: Messen Sie die Generierungszeit für verschiedene gridSizes

### 7. **Chunk-Boundary Handling**

**Problem**: Offsets an Chunk-Grenzen müssen konsistent sein.

**Lösung**: 
1. Height-Map berechnet für gesamten HexGrid + 1 Block Rand
2. Offsets nutzen diese Height-Map unabhängig von Chunk-Grenzen
3. Chunks werden erst am Ende gruppiert und gespeichert

### 8. **Package-Struktur**

```
world-control/src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/control/
├── generator/
│   ├── AbstractTerrainGenerator.java
│   ├── FlatWorldGenerator.java
│   ├── NormalWorldGenerator.java
│   └── HillyWorldGenerator.java
└── util/
    └── FastNoiseLite.java (optional)
```

### 9. **Job-Parameter Format**

**Beispiel REST API Call zum Erstellen eines Generator-Jobs**:

```json
POST /control/worlds/{worldId}/jobs
{
  "executor": "normal-world-generator",
  "type": "terrain-generation",
  "parameters": {
    "grid": "0:0",
    "layer": "terrain",
    "waterLevel": "62",
    "baseHeight": "64",
    "heightVariation": "32",
    "seed": "12345",
    "grassBlockTypeId": "w/310",
    "dirtBlockTypeId": "w/279",
    "sandBlockTypeId": "w/520",
    "waterBlockTypeId": "w/5000"
  },
  "priority": 5,
  "maxRetries": 2
}
```

### 10. **Performance-Optimierungen**

1. **Lazy Height-Map**: Nur Positionen berechnen, die tatsächlich im HexGrid liegen
2. **Batch-Insert**: Alle Chunks eines HexGrids in einem Batch speichern
3. **Parallel Processing**: Wenn mehrere HexGrids generiert werden, parallel Jobs verarbeiten (via JobProcessingScheduler)
4. **Caching**: Noise-Generator pro Job-Instanz cachen (nicht pro Block)

### Critical Files for Implementation

- `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/server/world-control/src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/control/generator/AbstractTerrainGenerator.java` - Base class providing shared logic for all generators (parameter parsing, entity loading, chunk processing, saving)

- `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/server/world-control/src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/control/generator/NormalWorldGenerator.java` - Core implementation to port from TypeScript, includes simplex noise generation and sophisticated offset calculation algorithm

- `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/server/world-shared/src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/shared/job/JobExecutor.java` - Interface that generators must implement (already exists, reference for implementation)

- `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/server/world-shared/src/main/java/de/mhus/nimbus/world/shared/layer/WLayerService.java` - Service for saving generated terrain chunks (already exists, reference for saveTerrainChunk method)

- `/Users/hummel/sources/mhus/nimbus-server/client/packages/test_server/src/world/generators/NormalGenerator.ts` - TypeScript reference implementation showing exact noise algorithms and offset calculations to port

